trans-unit.source: Provides a cursor model for navigating and editing XML data.
trans-unit.target: Inneholder en markør modell for navigering og redigering av XML-data.

trans-unit.source: The XPathNavigator class in the <xref:System.Xml.XPath?displayProperty=fullName> namespace is an abstract class which defines a cursor model for navigating and editing XML information items as instances of the XQuery 1.0 and XPath 2.0 Data Model.
trans-unit.target: Klassen XPathNavigator i den <xref:System.Xml.XPath?displayProperty=fullName>navneområde er en abstrakt klasse som definerer en markør modell for navigering og redigere XML informasjonselementene som forekomster av XQuery 1.0 og XPath 2.0 datamodellen.</xref:System.Xml.XPath?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: An XPathNavigator object is created from a class that implements the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable> interface such as the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> and <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> classes.
trans-unit.target: Et objekt med XPathNavigator som er opprettet fra en klasse som implementerer den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable>grensesnitt som den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>og <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument>klasser.</xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable>

trans-unit.source: XPathNavigator objects created by <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument> objects are read-only while XPathNavigator objects created by <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> objects can be edited.
trans-unit.target: XPathNavigator-objekter som er opprettet av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>objekter er skrivebeskyttet under XPathNavigator objekter som ble opprettet av <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument>objekter kan redigeres.</xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathDocument>

trans-unit.source: An XPathNavigator object's read-only or editable status is determined using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CanEdit%2A> property of the XPathNavigator class.
trans-unit.target: Objektets XPathNavigator fastslås skrivebeskyttet eller redigerbare ved hjelp av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CanEdit%2A>egenskapen for XPathNavigator klasse.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CanEdit%2A>

trans-unit.source: For more information about processing XML data using the XPath data model, see the [Process XML Data Using the XPath Data Model](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) topic.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon om behandling av XML-dataene ved hjelp av datamodellen XPath, se den [prosessen XML-dataene ved hjelp av datamodellen XPath](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) emnet.

trans-unit.source: > [!IMPORTANT] > Exceptions raised as a result of using the XPathNavigator class, such as the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathException> class, may contain sensitive information that should not be exposed in untrusted scenarios.
trans-unit.target: > [!IMPORTANT] > Unntak som starter ved å bruke XPathNavigator-klassen som den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathException>klasse, kan inneholde sensitiv informasjon som skal vises i uklarerte scenarier.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathException>

trans-unit.source: Exceptions should be properly handled so that this sensitive information is not exposed in untrusted scenarios.
trans-unit.target: Unntak skal behandles riktig slik at denne sensitiv informasjon ikke er eksponert i uklarerte scenarier.

trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.target: Denne konstruktøren kalles av utledede klassen brukes til å initialisere tilstand i denne typen.

trans-unit.source: Returns an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to create one or more new child nodes at the end of the list of child nodes of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å opprette en eller flere nye underordnede noder på slutten av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Appending child nodes adds the new nodes to the end of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Legge til underordnede noder legger til nye noder på slutten av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the first appended node becomes the fourth child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for et element, blir den første føyer noden fjerde underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the AppendChild method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta ved AppendChild-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - The new child node is not inserted until the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object is called.
trans-unit.target: -Nye underordnet node er ikke satt til den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet kalles.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> </xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChild method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the root node or an element node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden AppendChild er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert i rotnoden eller en elementnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChild method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden AppendChild påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: You can write more than one node to the writer.
trans-unit.target: Du kan skrive flere noder til skriveren.

trans-unit.source: All nodes are appended to the end of the list of child nodes of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Alle noder legges til slutten av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to create new child nodes at the end of the list of child nodes of the current node.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å opprette nye underordnede noder på slutten av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Creates a new child node at the end of the list of child nodes of the current node using the XML data string specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en ny underordnet node på slutten av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden ved hjelp av den angitte strengen for XML-data.

trans-unit.source: Appending a child node adds the new node to the end of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Tilføyer en underordnet node legger til noden for nye til slutten av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the appended node becomes the fourth child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for et element, blir noden føyer fjerde underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: To create a new element node, include all XML syntax in the XML string parameter.
trans-unit.target: Inkluder alle XML-syntaksen i XML-strengparameter for å opprette en ny elementnode.

trans-unit.source: The string for a new `book` node is `AppendChild("<book/>")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for en ny `book` noden `AppendChild("<book/>")`.

trans-unit.source: The string for appending the text "book" to the current node's text node is `AppendChild("book")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for tilføyer teksten "book" til den gjeldende noden Tekstnoden er `AppendChild("book")`.

trans-unit.source: If the XML string contains multiple nodes, all nodes are added.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-strengen inneholder flere noder, legges til alle noder.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the AppendChild method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta ved AppendChild-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChild method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the root node or an element node.

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChild method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden AppendChild påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Creates a new child element node at the end of the list of child nodes of the current node using the namespace prefix, local name and namespace URI specified with the value specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en ny underordnet elementnode på slutten av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden ved hjelp av navneområdeprefikset, lokalt navn og navneområde-URI som er angitt med verdien som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: Appending a child node adds the new node to the end of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Tilføyer en underordnet node legger til noden for nye til slutten av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element node, the appended node becomes the fourth child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for en element-noden, blir noden føyer fjerde underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: Namespace prefix and URI values can be obtained by using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A> method or the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Namespace prefiks og URI-verdier kan hente ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>metoden eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A>metode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the following syntax appends a child element by using the in-scope namespace `xmlns:bk=http://www.contoso.com/books`: ``` navigator.AppendChildElement(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` This creates the new child `<bk:pages/>` element.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel følgende syntaks tilføyer et underordnet element ved hjelp av navneområdet i omfanget `xmlns:bk=http://www.contoso.com/books`: ``` navigator.AppendChildElement(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` dette oppretter den nye underordnet `<bk:pages/>` elementet.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the AppendChildElement method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker AppendChildElement-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the namespace prefix specified is `null` or <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, then the prefix for the namespace URI of the new element is obtained from the current namespaces in-scope.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis navneområdeprefikset angitt `null` eller <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, og deretter prefikset for navneområde-URI for nytt element er hentet fra gjeldende navneområdene i omfanget.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If there is no namespace prefix assigned to the specified namespace URI at the current scope, then a namespace prefix is automatically generated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ingen navneområdeprefiks som er tilordnet til det angitte navneområdet-URI i gjeldende omfang, genereres automatisk et navneområdeprefiks.

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChildElement method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the root node or an element node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden AppendChildElement er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert i rotnoden eller en elementnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The AppendChildElement method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden AppendChildElement påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The namespace prefix of the new child element node (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområdeprefikset for ny underordnet elementnode (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: The local name of the new child element node (if any).
trans-unit.target: Lokale navnet på den nye underordnet element noden (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI of the new child element node (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområde-URI for ny underordnet elementnode (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.target: <xref:System.String>og <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> er like.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.target: Verdien for den nye underordnede element noden.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.String> or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> are passed, an empty element is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.String>eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> sendes, et tomt element er opprettet.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the base URI for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter basis-URIEN for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: A networked XML document is comprised of chunks of data, aggregated using various W3C standard inclusion mechanisms, and therefore contains nodes that come from different places.
trans-unit.target: Et nettverk XML-dokument består av biter av data aggregeres med ulike W3C standard inkluderings mekanismer, og derfor inneholder noder som kommer fra ulike steder.

trans-unit.source: DTD entities are an example of this aggregated data, but it is not limited to DTDs.
trans-unit.target: DTD enheter er et eksempel på denne aggregerte data, men det er ikke begrenset til DTDer.

trans-unit.source: The BaseURI property tells you where these nodes originate from.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen BaseURI forteller der disse nodene stammer fra.

trans-unit.source: For example, if the XML data is loaded from http://server/mydata.xml, the BaseURI property returns http://server/mydata.xml.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-dataene er lastet inn fra http://server/mydata.xml, returnerer egenskapen BaseURI http://server/mydata.xml.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Nodes created using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> class have the same BaseURI as the XML document the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> was created from.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Noder som er opprettet ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>klassen har samme BaseURI som XML-dokument i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>ble opprettet fra.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The location from which the node was loaded, or <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if there is no value.
trans-unit.target: Plasseringen som noden ble lastet inn fra, eller <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> Hvis ingen verdi.

trans-unit.source: Gets a value indicating whether the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> can edit the underlying XML data.

trans-unit.source: The CanEdit property has different values based on the three different implementations of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable> interface in the .NET Framework.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen CanEdit har forskjellige verdier som er basert på tre forskjellige implementeringer av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable>grensesnittet i .NET Framework.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.IXPathNavigable>

trans-unit.source: The CanEdit values for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> objects created by each implementation are listed in the following table.
trans-unit.target: CanEdit verdier for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objekter som ble opprettet av hver implementeringen vises i følgende tabell.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> can edit the underlying XML data; otherwise <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> kan redigere de underliggende XML-dataene; ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Verifies that the XML data in the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> conforms to the XML Schema definition language (XSD) schema provided.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollerer at XML-dataene i den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> overholder angitt XML-skjema definition language (XSD) skjemaet.

trans-unit.source: - The CheckValidity method verifies that the XML data contained in the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> conforms to a global type or declaration in the schema or schemas provided in the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden "CheckValidity" bekrefter at XML-dataene i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>samsvar med en global type eller deklarasjonen i skjemaet eller XML-skjemaer i <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>.</xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The CheckValidity method does not perform infoset augmentation.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden "CheckValidity" utfører ikke infoset styrkes.

trans-unit.source: This means that schema defaults are not applied, text values are not converted to atomic values, and no new type information is associated with information items.
trans-unit.target: Dette betyr at skjemaet standarder brukes ikke, tekstverdier ikke konverteres til atomic verdier, og ingen nye typeinformasjonen er knyttet til informasjonselementene.

trans-unit.source: - Schema `xsi:schemaLocation` or `xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation` hints in the XML data of are ignored.
trans-unit.target: -Skjema `xsi:schemaLocation` eller `xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation` -tips i XML-data for ignoreres.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on a document node, the validation process includes checking of uniqueness and reference constraints (`xs:ID`, `xs:IDREF`, `xs:key`, `xs:keyref`, and `xs:unique`).
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en Dokumentnode inkluderer valideringen kontroll av begrensninger for unikhet og referanse (`xs:ID`, `xs:IDREF`, `xs:key`, `xs:keyref`, og `xs:unique`).</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, these checks are omitted.
trans-unit.target: Ellers er disse kontrollene utelatt.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet> passed as a parameter is `null` and the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element node, the type information exposed by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property's <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A> property is used to check the node's validity.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>sendt som en parameter er `null` og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en element-noden, av typen informasjon som vises av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>egenskapens <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A>egenskapen brukes til å kontrollere nodens gyldighetsperiode.</xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet> passed as a parameter is `null` and the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the root node, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property of the document element (that is, the element child of the root node) is used.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>sendt som en parameter er `null` og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på rotnoden, den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>for dokumentelementet (det vil si elementet underordnet rotnoden) brukes.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>

trans-unit.source: In both cases if the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A> property of the element's <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property is `null` and the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet> passed as a parameter is `null`, an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> is thrown because there is no type information to use to perform validation.
trans-unit.target: I begge tilfeller hvis den <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A>for elementets <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>egenskapen `null` og <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet>sendt som en parameter er `null`, en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>et fordi det finnes ingen typeinformasjon som skal brukes til å utføre validering.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet"></xref> containing the schemas used to validate the XML data contained in the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaSet"> </xref> som inneholder skjemaer som brukes til å validere XML-dataene i den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.ValidationEventHandler"></xref> that receives information about schema validation warnings and errors.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.ValidationEventHandler"> </xref> som mottar informasjon om skjemaet Valideringsadvarsler og feil.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is positioned on a node that is not an element, attribute, or the root node or there is not type information to perform validation.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er plassert på en node som ikke er et element, attributt, eller rotnoden eller det er ikke informasjon om å utføre validering.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, creates a new <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> positioned at the same node as this <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, oppretter du en ny <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> plassert i samme node som dette <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The Clone method is especially useful in conjunction with the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>.
trans-unit.target: Metoden klone er spesielt nyttig sammen med <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator> is used to iterate over a selected node set, and contains a <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A> property which returns an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> positioned on the context node of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>brukes til å oppdatere en valgte nodesett, og inneholder en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A>egenskap som returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på kontekstnoden for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>

trans-unit.source: However, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> returned by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A> property cannot be used to move away from the node set.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>returnert av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A>egenskapen kan ikke brukes til å flytte fra nodesettet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Instead, you clone the returned <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> and use the cloned navigator to do any additional moves.
trans-unit.target: I stedet du klone den returnerte <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>og bruker klonede navigatoren noen ekstra trekk.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The cloned <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is not affected by subsequent changes to the original <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Det klonede <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>påvirkes ikke av senere endringer i opprinnelige <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: A new <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> positioned at the same node as this <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: En ny <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> plassert i samme node som dette <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Compares the position of the current <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> with the position of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> specified.

trans-unit.source: The following table describes the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder> enumeration.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor beskriver det <xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>opplisting.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>

trans-unit.source: |XmlNodeOrder|Description| |------------------|-----------------| |<xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>|The current node of this <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is before the current node of the supplied <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.| |<xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>|The current node of this <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is after the current node of the supplied <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.| |<xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>|The two <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> objects are positioned on the same node.| |<xref:System.Xml.XmlNodeOrder>|The node positions cannot be determined relative to each other in the document order, or `null` is specified as the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> parameter.

trans-unit.source: This could occur if the two nodes reside in different trees.| The ComparePosition method's behavior is dependent on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is currently positioned on.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan skje hvis de to nodene befinner seg på forskjellige trær. | Metoden ComparePosition virkemåte er avhengig av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>for øyeblikket er plassert på.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: When comparing nodes in the XML document, the following rules apply: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes: These nodes are returned in document order from the source document.
trans-unit.target: Sammenlignet nodene i XML-dokumentet, gjelder følgende regler:- <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder: disse nodene returneres i dokumentrekkefølgen fra kildedokumentet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes: These nodes may be returned in document order and are always before the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes of the parent element.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder: disse nodene kan returneres i dokumentrekkefølgen og er alltid før den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder for det overordnede elementet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes: These nodes may be returned in document order.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder: disse nodene kan returneres i dokumentrekkefølgen.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: They always come after the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes and before any child nodes of the parent node.
trans-unit.target: De kommer alltid etter den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder og før alle underordnede noder av den overordnede noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: Compiles a string representing an XPath expression and returns an <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"></xref> object.
trans-unit.target: Kompilerer en streng som representerer et XPath-uttrykk og returnerer en <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"> </xref> objektet.

trans-unit.source: An XPath expression is evaluated to yield one of the following return types: - Node Set: an unordered collection of nodes without duplicates - Boolean: `true` or `false` - Number: a floating-point number - String: a sequence of UCS characters Expressions that return a node set can be used in the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A> and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: En XPath-uttrykket blir evaluert til ytelse på følgende Returtypen:-Node Set: en usortert samling av noder uten duplikater - boolsk: `true` eller `false` - nummer: et flyttall - streng: en tegnsekvens UCS-uttrykk som returnerer et nodesett kan brukes i den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A>og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>metoder.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A>

trans-unit.source: Expressions that return a Boolean, number, or string can be used in the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Uttrykk som returnerer en boolsk verdi, et tall eller en streng som kan brukes i den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>

trans-unit.source: The rules on valid expressions for the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A> method are specific to that method.
trans-unit.target: Reglene på gyldig uttrykk for den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A>metoden som er spesifikke for denne metoden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A>

trans-unit.source: Creates an attribute node on the current element node using the namespace prefix, local name and namespace URI specified with the value specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en attributtnode for gjeldende element noden ved hjelp av navneområdeprefikset, lokalt navn og navneområde-URI som er angitt med verdien som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: Namespace prefix and URI values can be obtained using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A> or <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Namespace prefiks og URI-verdier kan hentes ved hjelp av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A>metode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the following syntax creates an attribute by using the in-scope namespace `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` editor.CreateAttribute(navigator.Prefix, "attributeName", LookupNamespace(navigator.Prefix), "text") ``` This creates the new attribute `<bk:element attributeName="text"/>` on the current element.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel følgende syntaks oppretter et attributt ved hjelp av navneområdet i omfanget `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` editor.CreateAttribute(navigator.Prefix, "attributeName", LookupNamespace(navigator.Prefix), "text") ``` dette oppretter det nye attributtet `<bk:element attributeName="text"/>` for gjeldende element.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the CreateAttribute method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker CreateAttribute-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the namespace prefix specified is <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> or `null`, the prefix for the namespace URI of the new attribute is obtained from the current namespaces in-scope.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis navneområdeprefikset angitt <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>eller `null`, prefikset for navneområde-URI for det nye attributtet er hentet fra gjeldende navneområdene i omfanget.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If there is no namespace prefix assigned to the specified namespace URI at the current scope, a namespace prefix is automatically generated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ingen navneområdeprefiks som er tilordnet til det angitte navneområdet-URI i gjeldende omfang, er et navneområdeprefiks automatisk generert.

trans-unit.source: For example to create a new attribute on an element in the default namespace of the `contosoBooks.xml` file, (`xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"`), you specify `null` or <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> for both the namespace prefix and namespace URI parameters.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel opprette et nytt attributt i et element i standard navneområde i `contosoBooks.xml` filen (`xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"`), du angir `null` eller <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>for navneområdeprefikset og navneområdet URI parametere.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Specifying `http://www.contoso.com/books` as the namespace URI parameter will cause the CreateAttribute method to auto generate a namespace prefix for the new attribute.
trans-unit.target: Angir `http://www.contoso.com/books` som parameter for navneområde-URI vil føre til at CreateAttribute-metode for å automatisk generere et navneområdeprefiks for det nye attributtet.

trans-unit.source: - If the new attribute created is a namespace node which conflicts with a namespace declaration on the element, either because the namespace prefix chosen is used by another namespace declaration at the same scope, or because the prefix chosen is the same as that of the element but is bound to a different namespace URI, an exception is thrown.

trans-unit.source: Returns an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to create new attributes on the current element.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å opprette nye attributter for gjeldende element.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the CreateAttributes method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker CreateAttributes-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - When the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element, the new attributes created by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> method are placed at the end of the attribute list of the current element.
trans-unit.target: -Når den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementet nye attributter som er opprettet av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>metoden plasseres på slutten av listen over attributter for gjeldende element.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The new attributes are not inserted until the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object is called.
trans-unit.target: -Nye attributter er ikke satt til den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet kalles.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> </xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If the namespace prefix specified is <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> or `null`, the prefix for the namespace URI of the new attribute is obtained from the current namespaces in-scope.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis navneområdeprefikset angitt <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>eller `null`, prefikset for navneområde-URI for det nye attributtet er hentet fra gjeldende navneområdene i omfanget.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If there is no namespace prefix assigned to the specified namespace URI at the current scope, a namespace prefix is automatically generated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ingen navneområdeprefiks som er tilordnet til det angitte navneområdet-URI i gjeldende omfang, er et navneområdeprefiks automatisk generert.

trans-unit.source: For example to create a new attribute on an element in the default namespace of the `contosoBooks.xml` file, (`xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"`), you specify `null` or <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> for both the namespace prefix and namespace URI parameters.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel opprette et nytt attributt i et element i standard navneområde i `contosoBooks.xml` filen (`xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"`), du angir `null` eller <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>for navneområdeprefikset og navneområdet URI parametere.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Specifying `http://www.contoso.com/books` as the namespace URI parameter will cause the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CreateAttribute%2A> method to auto generate a namespace prefix for the new attribute.
trans-unit.target: Angir `http://www.contoso.com/books` som navneområde-URI parameteren vil føre til at den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CreateAttribute%2A>metode for å automatisk generere et navneområdeprefiks for det nye attributtet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.CreateAttribute%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If the new attribute created is a namespace node which conflicts with a namespace declaration on the element, either because the namespace prefix chosen is used by another namespace declaration at the same scope, or because the prefix chosen is the same as that of the element but is bound to a different namespace URI, an exception is thrown.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis det nye attributtet opprettet en navneområdenode som er i konflikt med en navneområdedeklarasjon i elementet fordi navneområdeprefikset valgt brukes av en annen navneområdedeklarasjon i samme omfang, eller fordi prefikset valgte er den samme som elementet, men er bundet til et annet navneområde-URI, et unntak.

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object returned may only be used to create attributes.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>Objektet som ble returnert kan bare brukes til å opprette attributter.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Calling other <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object methods that do not create attributes throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: Kaller andre <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektmetoder som ikke Opprett attributter oppstår det et unntak.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Deletes a range of sibling nodes from the current node to the node specified.
trans-unit.target: Sletter en rekke likestilte noder fra den gjeldende noden noden som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: The DeleteRange method deletes a range of sibling nodes from the current node the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on (inclusive) to the node specified by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> parameter (inclusive).
trans-unit.target: Metoden DeleteRange sletter en rekke likestilte noder fra den gjeldende noden den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på (inklusiv) av noden som er angitt av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>parameteren (inklusiv).</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is then positioned on its parent node.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>deretter er plassert i den overordnede noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> positioned on the last sibling node in the range to delete.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> plasseres på den siste sideordnede-noden i intervallet som skal slettes.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> specified is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.

trans-unit.source: The last node to delete specified is not a valid sibling node of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Den siste noden slette er ikke en gyldig sideordnet node for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Deletes the current node and its child nodes.
trans-unit.target: Sletter den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene.

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the deleted node's parent node on successful deletion.
trans-unit.target: -Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på den slettede noden overordnet node på vellykket sletting.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - If the deleted node is a text node which is the content of a simple typed element, the element loses its type information.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den slettede noden er en text-node som er innholdet i et enkelt typeangitt element, mister elementet typeinformasjonen.

trans-unit.source: This means that when positioned on the element the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.XmlType%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ValueType%2A> and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.TypedValue%2A> properties have the values `null`, <xref:System.String> and <xref:System.String.Empty> respectively.
trans-unit.target: Dette betyr at når plasseres på elementet i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.XmlType%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ValueType%2A>og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.TypedValue%2A>egenskapene har verdiene `null`, <xref:System.String>og <xref:System.String.Empty>henholdsvis.</xref:System.String.Empty> </xref:System.String> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.TypedValue%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ValueType%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.XmlType%2A>

trans-unit.source: - Deleted nodes are still accessible to <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> objects positioned over them prior to deletion.
trans-unit.target: -Slettet noder er fortsatt tilgjengelige for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objekter som er plassert over dem før sletting.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: However methods that attempt to move away from the deleted sub-tree fail.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid metoder som forsøk på å flytte fra det slettede undertreet mislykkes.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A> and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A> methods always fail when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned over the top most deleted node.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A>og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A>metoder alltid mislykkes når den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert over den øverste noden mest slettet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A>

trans-unit.source: This is because the deleted node is no longer connected to the XML document.
trans-unit.target: Dette er fordi noden slettet ikke lenger er knyttet til XML-dokumentet.

trans-unit.source: Similarly the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A> method always fails if the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the bottom-most deleted node.
trans-unit.target: På samme måte i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>metoden alltid mislykkes hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på noden nederst slettet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is positioned on a node that cannot be deleted such as the root node or a namespace node.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er plassert på en node som ikke kan slettes for eksempel rotnoden eller en navneområdenode.

trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> støtter ikke redigering.

trans-unit.source: Evaluates the specified XPath expression and returns the typed result.

trans-unit.source: The following C# code converts the `Price/text()` node to a number, multiplies it by 10, and returns the resulting value.
trans-unit.target: Følgende C# kode konverterer den `Price/text()` node til et tall, multipliserer den med 10, og returnerer den resulterende verdien.

trans-unit.source: ``` nav.Evaluate("Price/text()*10"); ``` > [!NOTE] > The XPath position() and last() functions, unless used as a predicate in a location step, require a reference to a node set in order to be evaluated.
trans-unit.target: ``` nav.Evaluate("Price/text()*10"); ``` > [!NOTE]> XPath position() og last() funksjonene, krever Hvis ikke brukes som et predikat i et plassering-trinn en referanse til en node som er angitt for å returnere.

trans-unit.source: In this case, you must use the overload which takes an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator> as an argument; otherwise, position() and last() return 0.
trans-unit.target: I så fall må du bruke overlasten som tar en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>som et argument; ellers position() og last() returnerer 0.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeIterator>

trans-unit.source: If `context` is `null`, the node on which the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is currently positioned is used as the context node.
trans-unit.target: Hvis `context` er `null`, noden som den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>for øyeblikket er plassert brukes som kontekstnoden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The position() and last() functions, unless used as a predicate in a location step, always return 0 under the following conditions: - The `context` argument is `null`.

trans-unit.source: Creates a new sibling node before the currently selected node using the XML string specified.

trans-unit.source: To create a new element node, include all XML syntax in the XML string parameter.

trans-unit.source: The string for a new `book` node is `InsertBefore("<book/>")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for en ny `book` noden `InsertBefore("<book/>")`.

trans-unit.source: The string for inserting the text "book" before the current node's text node is `InsertBefore("book")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for å sette inn teksten "book" før den gjeldende noden tekstnode `InsertBefore("book")`.

trans-unit.source: If the XML string contains multiple nodes, all nodes are added.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-strengen inneholder flere noder, legges til alle noder.

trans-unit.source: Creates a new sibling element after the current node using the namespace prefix, local name and namespace URI specified, with the value specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter et nytt likestilte element etter den gjeldende noden ved hjelp av navneområdeprefikset, lokalt navn og navneområde-URI som er angitt, med den angitte verdien.

trans-unit.source: Namespace prefix and URI values can be obtained using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A> or <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Namespace prefiks og URI-verdier kan hentes ved hjelp av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A>metode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the following syntax inserts a sibling element by using the in-scope namespace `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` navigator.InsertElementAfter(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` This creates the new sibling `<bk:pages/>` element.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel følgende syntaks setter inn et likestilte element ved hjelp av navneområdet i omfanget `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` navigator.InsertElementAfter(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` dette oppretter den nye sideordnet `<bk:pages/>` elementet.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the InsertElementAfter method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker InsertElementAfter-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the namespace prefix specified is `null` or <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, then the prefix for the namespace URI of the new element is obtained from the current namespaces in-scope.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis navneområdeprefikset angitt `null` eller <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, og deretter prefikset for navneområde-URI for nytt element er hentet fra gjeldende navneområdene i omfanget.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If there is no namespace prefix assigned to the specified namespace URI at the current scope, then a namespace prefix is automatically generated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ingen navneområdeprefiks som er tilordnet til det angitte navneområdet-URI i gjeldende omfang, genereres automatisk et navneområdeprefiks.

trans-unit.source: - The InsertElementAfter method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element, text, processing instruction, or comment node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden InsertElementAfter er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementet, tekst, behandlingsinstruksjon eller kommentarnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The InsertElementAfter method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden InsertElementAfter påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The namespace prefix of the new child element (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområdeprefikset for nytt underordnet element (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.target: Lokale navnet på det nye underordnet elementet (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI of the new child element (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområde-URI for nytt underordnet element (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the specified <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is a descendant of the current <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Bestemmer om den angitte <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er en etterkommer av gjeldende <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is a descendant of the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> if it is positioned on a descendant node of the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er en etterkommer av den gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>Hvis den er plassert på en underordnede noden for gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Take, for example, the following XML string: `<item><name>widget</name></item>` If the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the `item` node, and the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified is positioned on the `name` node, IsDescendant returns `true`.
trans-unit.target: Ta, for eksempel følgende XML-strengen: `<item><name>widget</name></item>` Hvis gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på den `item` noden, og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitte plasseres på den `name` noden, IsDescendant returnerer `true`.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: This method always returns `false` under the following conditions: - The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified shares the same implementation but points at a different document instance than the current navigator.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden returnerer alltid `false` følgende betingelser: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitte deler samme implementering men peker på et annet dokument serverforekomsten enn gjeldende navigatoren.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified has a different implementation than the current navigator.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>Angitte har en annen implementering enn gjeldende navigatoren.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets a value indicating whether the current node is an empty element without an end element tag.

trans-unit.source: This property enables you to determine the difference between the following different elements.
trans-unit.target: Denne egenskapen kan du bestemme forskjellen mellom følgende forskjellige elementer.

trans-unit.source: |Element|IsEmptyElement Value| |-------------|--------------------------| |`<item num="123"/>`|`true`| |`<item num="123">test</item>`|`false`| |`<item num="123"></item>`|`false`|
trans-unit.target: | Elementet | Verdien for IsEmptyElement | |-------------|--------------------------| | `<item num="123"/>`|`true`| | `<item num="123">test</item>`|`false`| |`<item num="123"></item>`|`false`|

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the current node is an empty element; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis den gjeldende noden er et tomt element; Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Gets a value indicating if the current node represents an XPath node.
trans-unit.target: Henter en verdi som angir om den gjeldende noden representerer en XPath-node.

trans-unit.source: Always returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer alltid <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, determines whether the current <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is at the same position as the specified <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, bestemmer om gjeldende <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er i samme posisjon som den angitte <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The IsSamePosition method assumes that the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified shares the same implementation and is points at the same document instance as the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Metoden IsSamePosition antar at det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitte deler samme implementeringen og er punkt på samme dokumentet-forekomst som gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: This method always returns `false` under the following conditions: - The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified shares the same implementation but points at a different document instance than the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden returnerer alltid `false` følgende betingelser:- <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitt deler samme implementering men peker på et annet dokument-forekomst enn gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> has a different implementation than the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>Har en annen implementering enn gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to compare to this <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> til å sammenligne dette <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the two <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> objects have the same position; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis to <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> objekter har samme; ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name*> of the current node without any namespace prefix.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name*>for den gjeldende noden uten noen navneområdeprefikset.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name*>

trans-unit.source: The local name returned depends on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Lokale returnerte navnet på avhenger av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: For example, the local name for the `<bk:book>` element is `book`.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel lokalt navn for den `<bk:book>` elementet `book`.

trans-unit.source: The following table lists the value returned by the LocalName property, based on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor viser verdien som returneres av LocalName-egenskapen, basert på den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: |XPathNodeType|Property Value| |-------------------|--------------------| |<xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>|The local name of the element.| |<xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>|The local name of the attribute.| |<xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>|The prefix associated with the namespace URI.| |<xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>|The target of the processing instruction.| |All other <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes|<xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>.|
trans-unit.target: | XPathNodeType | Egenskapsverdien | |-------------------|--------------------| | <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>| Det lokale navnet på elementet. | | <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>| Det lokale navnet på attributtet. | | <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>| Prefikset tilknyttet navneområde-URI. | | <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>| Målet for behandlingsinstruksjonen. | | Alle andre <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder |<xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>. |</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the local name of the current node, or <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if the current node does not have a name (for example, text or comment nodes).
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder det lokale navnet på den gjeldende noden eller <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> hvis den gjeldende noden ikke har navn (for eksempel tekst eller kommentar noder).</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Gets the namespace URI for the specified prefix.
trans-unit.target: Henter navneområde-URI for det angitte prefikset.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> is specified as the `prefix` parameter, the currently assigned default namespace URI is returned.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName>er angitt som den `prefix` parameteren, som er tilordnet standard navneområde URI returneres.</xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If no default namespace URI is explicitly assigned, and <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> is specified as the `prefix` parameter, the blank prefix is associated with elements that are not in any namespace, and <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> is returned.
trans-unit.target: Hvis ingen standard navneområder URI er eksplisitt tilordnet, og <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>er angitt som den `prefix` , tomme prefikset er knyttet til elementer som ikke finnes i navneområder, og <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName>returneres.</xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The prefix to namespace URI mappings can change from node to node in an XML document.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Prefiks til navneområde-URI-tilordninger kan endre fra noden til-node i et XML-dokument.

trans-unit.source: As a result, the value of the LookupNamespace method may not be consistent from one node to the next.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for metoden LookupNamespace kan derfor ikke være konsekvent fra én node til neste.

trans-unit.source: The prefix whose namespace URI you want to resolve.
trans-unit.target: Prefikset der navneområde-URI du vil løse.

trans-unit.source: To match the default namespace, pass <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil samsvare med standard navneområde, kan du sende <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName>.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace URI assigned to the namespace prefix specified; <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> if no namespace URI is assigned to the prefix specified.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder navneområdet URI tilordnet navneområdet prefikset som er angitt. <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> Hvis ingen navneområdet URI er tilordnet prefikset som er angitt.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.String> returned is atomized.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.String>returnerte er oppdelt.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Gets the prefix declared for the specified namespace URI.
trans-unit.target: Henter prefikset deklarert for det angitte navneområdet-URI.

trans-unit.source: The LookupPrefix method returns the first prefix that matches the namespace URI specified.
trans-unit.target: Metoden LookupPrefix returnerer første prefikset som samsvarer med navneområde-URI som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: Multiple prefixes referring to the same namespace URI are not ordered in any particular way, so a particular prefix may not be returned each time when more than one is assigned.
trans-unit.target: Flere prefikser refererer til samme navneområde URI sorteres ikke på noen bestemt måte, slik at et bestemt prefiks ikke kan returneres hver gang når flere er tilordnet.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Namespace URI to prefix mappings can change from node to node in an XML document.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Namespace URIEN som prefiks tilordninger kan endre fra noden til-node i et XML-dokument.

trans-unit.source: As a result, the value of the LookupPrefix method may not be consistent from one node to the next.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for metoden LookupPrefix kan derfor ikke være konsekvent fra én node til neste.

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI to resolve for the prefix.
trans-unit.target: Navneområde-URI til å løse for prefikset.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace prefix assigned to the namespace URI specified; otherwise, <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if no prefix is assigned to the namespace URI specified.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder navneområdeprefikset tildelt navneområde-URI angitt; ellers <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> Hvis ingen prefiks er tilordnet til navneområde-URI som er angitt.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.String> returned is atomized.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.String>returnerte er oppdelt.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis den gjeldende noden samsvarer med det angitte XPath-uttrykket. Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.target: Bestemmer om den gjeldende noden samsvarer med den angitte <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: This method is identical to the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method, except that a <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> object containing the compiled XPath expression is specified, rather than an XPath expression <xref:System.String>.

trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"> </xref> objektet som inneholder kompilerte XPath-uttrykket.

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the current node matches the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"></xref>; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis den gjeldende noden samsvarer med den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression"> </xref>; ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The XPath expression cannot be evaluated.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, moves the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to the same position as the specified <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, flyttes av <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> til samme posisjon som den angitte <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: This method always returns `true` if the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified is an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> that shares the same implementation and points at the same document instance as the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden returnerer alltid `true` Hvis <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitt er en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>som deler samme implementering og peker på den samme dokumentforekomsten som gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: This method always returns `false` if the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> specified is an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> that has a different implementation than the current <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden returnerer alltid `false` Hvis <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>angitt, er en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>som har en annen implementering enn gjeldende <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> positioned on the node that you want to move to.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> plasseres på noden som du ønsker å flytte til.

trans-unit.source: Returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is successful moving to the same position as the specified <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""> </xref> hvis den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er vellykket bytte til samme posisjon som den angitte <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>; ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: If <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>, the position of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is unchanged.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>, posisjonen for den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> uendret.

trans-unit.source: Moves the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to the attribute with the matching local name and namespace URI.
trans-unit.target: Flytter den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> for attributtet med samsvarende lokalt navn og navneområde-URI.

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is not currently positioned on an element, this method returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er ikke for øyeblikket er plassert i et element metoden returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: After a successful call to MoveToAttribute, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LocalName%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.NamespaceURI%2A> and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Prefix%2A> properties reflect the values of the attribute.
trans-unit.target: Etter en vellykket kall til MoveToAttribute, den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LocalName%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.NamespaceURI%2A>og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Prefix%2A>Egenskaper gjenspeiler verdiene for attributtet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Prefix%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.NamespaceURI%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LocalName%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an attribute, the methods <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A>, and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A> are not applicable.
trans-unit.target: Når den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en attributt metodene <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A>, og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A>gjelder ikke.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: These methods always return `false` and do not change the position of the navigator.
trans-unit.target: Disse metodene alltid returnere `false` og endres ikke posisjonen for navigatoren.

trans-unit.source: Rather, you can call <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextAttribute%2A> to move to the next attribute node.
trans-unit.target: Du kan kaller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextAttribute%2A>å flytte til neste attributtnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextAttribute%2A>

trans-unit.source: Once positioned on an attribute, you can call <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A> to move to the owner element.
trans-unit.target: Når plasseres på et attributt, kan du kalle <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A>å flytte til elementet eieren.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A>

trans-unit.source: The local name of the attribute.
trans-unit.target: Lokale navnet på attributtet.

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI of the attribute; <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> for an empty namespace.
trans-unit.target: Navneområde-URI til attributtet. <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> for et tomt navneområde.

trans-unit.source: Returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is successful moving to the attribute; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""> </xref> hvis den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er vellykket bytte til attributtet; ellers, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: If <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>, the position of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is unchanged.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>, posisjonen for den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> uendret.

trans-unit.source: The return value of the MoveToChild method depends on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node, and the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the child node to move to.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, moves to the node that has an attribute of type `ID` whose value matches the specified <xref:System.String>.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, flyttes til noden som har et attributt av typen `ID` som har en verdi som samsvarer med den angitte <xref:System.String>.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: This method can be used to identify nodes by unique `ID` provided the source document explicitly declares attributes of type `ID` using a DTD.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden kan brukes til å identifisere noder av unike `ID` angitt av kildedokument eksplisitt deklarerer attributter av typen `ID` ved hjelp av en DTD.

trans-unit.source: For example, suppose the following XML data, `<data><x a="a1"/></data>`, was loaded using a DTD that included the following: `<!ATTLIST x a ID #REQUIRED>`.
trans-unit.target: Tenk følgende XML-data, `<data><x a="a1"/></data>`, ble lastet inn med en DTD som inkludert følgende: `<!ATTLIST x a ID #REQUIRED>`.

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> was positioned somewhere in the XML data, calling `MoveToId("a1")` positions the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> on the element node `x`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert et eller annet sted i XML-dataene, kaller `MoveToId("a1")` posisjonen i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>på noden elementet `x`.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> representing the `ID` value of the node to which you want to move.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som representerer den `ID` verdien for noden som du ønsker å flytte.</xref:System.String>
