trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>, posisjon for navigatoren er uendret.

trans-unit.source: Moves the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to the namespace node with the specified namespace prefix.
trans-unit.target: Flytter den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> navneområde-noden med det angitte navneområdeprefikset.

trans-unit.source: After the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> has been moved to the namespace node, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A> property reflects the name of the namespace.
trans-unit.target: Etter den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er flyttet til noden navneområdet den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A>egenskapen gjenspeiler navnet på navneområdet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on a namespace node, the methods <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A>, and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A> are not applicable.
trans-unit.target: Når den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en navneområdenode, metodene <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A>, og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A>gjelder ikke.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToFirst%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToPrevious%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNext%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: These methods always return `false` and do not change the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Disse metodene alltid returnere `false` og endres ikke plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Rather, you can call <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextNamespace%2A> to move to the next namespace node.
trans-unit.target: Du kan kaller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextNamespace%2A>å gå til noden neste navneområde.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToNextNamespace%2A>

trans-unit.source: After the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on a namespace node, you can call <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A> to move back to the element node.
trans-unit.target: Etter den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en navneområdenode kan du kalle <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A>å gå tilbake til noden element.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.MoveToParent%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: For a definition of namespace nodes, see section 5.4 of the W3C XML Path Language (XPath) recommendation located at http://www.w3.org/TR/xpath#data-model.
trans-unit.target: En definisjon av navneområdenoder avsnittet 5.4 for W3C XML Path Language (XPath) anbefaler på http://www.w3.org/TR/xpath#data-model.

trans-unit.source: The namespace prefix of the namespace node.
trans-unit.target: Navneområdeprefikset av noden som navneområde.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, moves the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to the next sibling node of the current node.

trans-unit.source: Moves the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> to the root node that the current node belongs to.
trans-unit.target: Flytter den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> til rotnoden som den gjeldende noden tilhører.

trans-unit.source: All nodes belong to one and only one document.
trans-unit.target: Alle nodene som hører til bare ett dokumentet.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, this method is always successful.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden er derfor alltid vellykket.

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the qualified name of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter det kvalifiserte navnet på den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The Name returned depends on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Det returnerte navnet som er avhengig av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: For example, the name for the `<bk:book>` element is `bk:book`.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel navnet for den `<bk:book>` elementet `bk:book`.

trans-unit.source: The following table lists the value returned by the Name property, based on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen nedenfor viser verdien som returneres av Name-egenskapen, basert på den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.target: I eksemplet nedenfor `<bk:book>`, navnet på noden elementet er `bk:book`. | | <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>| Det kvalifiserte navnet på <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the qualified Name of the current node, or <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if the current node does not have a name (for example, text or comment nodes).
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder det kvalifiserte navnet på den gjeldende noden eller <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> hvis den gjeldende noden ikke har navn (for eksempel tekst eller kommentar noder).</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the namespace URI of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter navneområde-URI for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI returned depends on the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Navneområdet URI returnerte avhenger av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: The NamespaceURI property returns `urn:samples` for the node `<bk:book xmlns:bk='urn:samples'>`.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer de NamespaceURI `urn:samples` for noden `<bk:book xmlns:bk='urn:samples'>`.

trans-unit.source: Only <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType><xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> nodes can have a namespace URI.
trans-unit.target: Bare <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType><xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>noder kan ha en navneområde-URI.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType></xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace URI of the current node, or <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if the current node has no namespace URI.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder navneområde-URI for den gjeldende noden eller <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> hvis den gjeldende noden har ingen navneområde-URI.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable> of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>av den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref>.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable> stores atomized strings of any local name, namespace URI, and prefix used by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>Butikker oppdelt strenger for alle lokale, navneområde-URI, og prefikset som brukes av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>

trans-unit.source: This means that when the same <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A> is returned multiple times (like "book"), the same <xref:System.String> object is returned for that <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Dette betyr at når den samme <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A>returneres flere ganger (for eksempel "book"), i samme <xref:System.String>objekt returneres for at <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A> </xref:System.String> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Name%2A>

trans-unit.source: This makes it possible to write efficient code that does object comparisons on these strings, instead of expensive string comparisons.
trans-unit.target: Dette gjør det mulig å skrive effektiv kode som objekt sammenligninger i disse strenger i stedet for kostbar strengsammenligninger.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable> object enabling you to get the atomized version of a <xref:System.String> within the XML document.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>objektet slik at du kan få atomized versjon av en <xref:System.String>i XML-dokumentet.</xref:System.String> </xref:System.Xml.XmlNameTable>

trans-unit.source: Gets an <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer> used for equality comparison of <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: Henter en <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer>brukes for likhetssammenligning av <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> objekter.</xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer>

trans-unit.source: The NavigatorComparer property allows <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> objects to be compared on the basis of position rather than reference to the object.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen NavigatorComparer tillater <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objektene som skal sammenlignes på grunnlag av posisjonen i stedet for referanse til objektet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ComparePosition%2A> and <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A> methods implemented by this class are based on the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> objects passed as parameters.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ComparePosition%2A>og <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A>metodene som implementeres av denne klassen er basert på posisjonen for den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objekter ble sendt som parametere.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Object.Equals%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.ComparePosition%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A> method implemented by this class uses the properties of the node such as its local name and namespace URI to create a hash code for the node.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A>implementert av denne klassen brukes egenskaper for noden for eksempel lokale navn og navneområde-URI til å opprette en hash-kode for noden.</xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer> used for equality comparison of <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer>brukes for likhetssammenligning av <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> objekter.</xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType"></xref> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType"> </xref> for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: One of the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType"></xref> values representing the current node.
trans-unit.target: Én av de <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType"> </xref> verdiene som representerer den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the markup representing the opening and closing tags of the current node and its child nodes.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir markup som representerer innledende og avsluttende koder for den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the markup representing the opening and closing tags of the current node and its child nodes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder koder som representerer innledende og avsluttende koder for den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, gets the namespace prefix associated with the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, henter navneområdeprefikset knyttet til den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The Prefix property gets the namespace prefix associated with the current node.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen prefikset henter navneområdeprefikset knyttet til den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, the Prefix property returns `bk` for the `<bk:book>` element.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel egenskapen prefikset returnerer `bk` for den `<bk:book>` elementet.

trans-unit.source: If a prefix does not exist, or the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> of the current node is not <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> or <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>, the Prefix property returns <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis et prefiks ikke finnes eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>er ikke <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>, eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>, egenskapen prefikset returnerer <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType> den gjeldende noden</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNodeType>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace prefix associated with the current node.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder navneområdeprefikset knyttet til den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Returns an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to create a new child node at the beginning of the list of child nodes of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å opprette en ny underordnet node i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Prepending a child node adds the new node to the beginning of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Prepending en underordnet node legger til noden for nye i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the prepended node becomes the first child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for et element, blir noden prepended den første underordnede noden.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the PrependChild method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker PrependChild-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - The new child node is not inserted until the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object is called.
trans-unit.target: -Nye underordnet node er ikke satt til den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet kalles.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> </xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>

trans-unit.source: - The PrependChild method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden PrependChild er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The PrependChild method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden PrependChild påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to create a new child node at the beginning of the list of child nodes of the current node.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å opprette en ny underordnet node i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: The current node the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is positioned on does not allow a new child node to be prepended.
trans-unit.target: Den gjeldende noden den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er plassert på tillater ikke en ny underordnet node til settes foran.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> does not support editing.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> støtter ikke redigering.

trans-unit.source: Creates a new child node at the beginning of the list of child nodes of the current node using the XML string specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en ny underordnet node i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden ved hjelp av XML-strengen som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: Prepending a child node adds the new node to the beginning of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Prepending en underordnet node legger til noden for nye i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the prepended node becomes the first child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for et element, blir noden prepended den første underordnede noden.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: To create a new element node, include all XML syntax in the XML string parameter.
trans-unit.target: Inkluder alle XML-syntaksen i XML-strengparameter for å opprette en ny elementnode.

trans-unit.source: The string for a new `book` node is `PrependChild("<book/>")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for en ny `book` noden `PrependChild("<book/>")`.

trans-unit.source: The string for appending the text "book" to the current node's text node is `PrependChild("book")`.
trans-unit.target: Strengen for tilføyer teksten "book" til den gjeldende noden Tekstnoden er `PrependChild("book")`.

trans-unit.source: If the XML string contains multiple nodes, all nodes are added.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-strengen inneholder flere noder, legges til alle noder.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the PrependChild method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker PrependChild-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - The PrependChild method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element node.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the prepended node becomes the first child node.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.target: Prepending en underordnet node legger til noden for nye i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> object is positioned over a sequence of XML nodes, all the nodes in the sequence are added.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> does not support editing.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> støtter ikke redigering.

trans-unit.source: Creates a new child element at the beginning of the list of child nodes of the current node using the namespace prefix, local name, and namespace URI specified with the value specified.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter et nytt underordnet objekt i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder av den gjeldende noden ved hjelp av navneområdeprefikset, lokalt navn og navneområde-URI som er angitt med verdien som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: Prepending a child node adds the new node to the beginning of the list of child nodes for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Prepending en underordnet node legger til noden for nye i begynnelsen av listen over underordnede noder for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: For example, when three child nodes exist for an element, the prepended node becomes the first child node.
trans-unit.target: Når det finnes tre underordnede noder for et element, blir noden prepended den første underordnede noden.

trans-unit.source: If no child nodes exist, then a new child node is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det finnes ingen underordnede noder, opprettes en ny underordnet node.

trans-unit.source: Namespace prefix and URI values can be obtained by using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A> or <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Namespace prefiks og URI-verdier kan hente ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>eller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A>metode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupNamespace%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.LookupPrefix%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the following syntax prepends a child element by using the in-scope namespace `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` navigator.PrependChildElement(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` This creates the new child `<bk:pages/>` element.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel følgende syntaks setter inn et underordnet element ved hjelp av navneområdet i omfanget `xmlns:bk="http://www.contoso.com/books"`: ``` navigator.PrependChildElement(navigator.Prefix, "pages", LookupNamespaceURI(navigator.Prefix), String.Empty) ``` dette oppretter den nye underordnet `<bk:pages/>` elementet.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the PrependChildElement method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker PrependChildElement-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the namespace prefix specified is `null` or <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, then the prefix for the namespace URI of the new element is obtained from the current namespaces in-scope.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis navneområdeprefikset angitt `null` eller <xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>, og deretter prefikset for navneområde-URI for nytt element er hentet fra gjeldende navneområdene i omfanget.</xref:System.String.Empty?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If there is no namespace prefix assigned to the specified namespace URI at the current scope, then a namespace prefix is automatically generated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis det er ingen navneområdeprefiks som er tilordnet til det angitte navneområdet-URI i gjeldende omfang, genereres automatisk et navneområdeprefiks.

trans-unit.source: - The PrependChildElement method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden PrependChildElement er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The PrependChildElement method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden PrependChildElement påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The namespace prefix of the new child element (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområdeprefikset for nytt underordnet element (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: The local name of the new child element (if any).
trans-unit.target: Lokale navnet på det nye underordnet elementet (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: The namespace URI of the new child element (if any).
trans-unit.target: Navneområde-URI for nytt underordnet element (Hvis noen).

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.String> and <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> are equivalent.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.String>og <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> er like.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: The value of the new child element.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for det nye underordnede elementet.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.String> or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> are passed, an empty element is created.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.String>eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref> sendes, et tomt element er opprettet.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: The current node the <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is positioned on does not allow a new child node to be prepended.
trans-unit.target: Den gjeldende noden den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er plassert på tillater ikke en ny underordnet node til settes foran.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> does not support editing.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> støtter ikke redigering.

trans-unit.source: Returns an <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object that contains the current node and its child nodes.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objekt som inneholder den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object is created with the current node and its child nodes, the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object's <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Xml.ReadState>.
trans-unit.target: Når <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet er opprettet med den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektets <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A>er satt til <xref:System.Xml.ReadState>.</xref:System.Xml.ReadState> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object's <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A> method is called for the first time, the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> is moved to the current node of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: Når <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektets <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A>-metoden for første gang, <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>flyttes til den gjeldende noden for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: The new <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object continues to read until the end of the XML tree is reached.
trans-unit.target: Den nye <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet fortsetter å lese til slutten av XML-treet er nådd.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: At this point, the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A> method returns `false` and the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object's <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Xml.ReadState>.
trans-unit.target: Nå den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A>metoden returnerer `false` og <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektets <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A>er satt til <xref:System.Xml.ReadState>.</xref:System.Xml.ReadState> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.ReadState%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Changing the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Endre plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet ikke har innvirkning på plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: Namespace declarations for the in-scope namespaces of the current node are not inserted into the XML stream provided to the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object.
trans-unit.target: Namespace deklareringer for navneområdene i omfanget for den gjeldende noden er ikke satt inn i XML-strømmen som er angitt i <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > This behavior differs from the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.WriteSubtree%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Denne virkemåten er forskjellig fra den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.WriteSubtree%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.WriteSubtree%2A>

trans-unit.source: This method creates the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object with specific reader settings, and the module that uses this method has no control over those settings.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden oppretter den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objektet med bestemte leseren innstillinger og modulen som bruker denne metoden har ingen kontroll over disse innstillingene.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: For example, the reader returned by this method prohibits processing Data Type Definitions (DTDs).
trans-unit.target: Leseren returneres av denne metoden hindrer for eksempel behandling av datatypedefinisjoner (DTDer).

trans-unit.source: If the reader attempts to read a file that uses a DTD, it will throw an error, <xref:System.Xml.XmlException>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis leseren forsøker å lese en fil som bruker en DTD, vil den throw feilmeldingen <xref:System.Xml.XmlException>.</xref:System.Xml.XmlException>

trans-unit.source: The message for the exception will be `Unexpected DTD declaration`.
trans-unit.target: Meldingen for unntaket blir `Unexpected DTD declaration`.

trans-unit.source: You can change this behavior by implementing a custom <xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver> that returns an <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> with the desired <xref:System.Xml.XmlReaderSettings>.
trans-unit.target: Du kan endre dette problemet ved å implementere et egendefinert <xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver>som returnerer en <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>med den ønskede <xref:System.Xml.XmlReaderSettings>.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReaderSettings> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlResolver>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> object that contains the current node and its child nodes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>objekt som inneholder den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is not positioned on an element node or the root node.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er ikke plassert på en elementnode eller rotnoden.

trans-unit.source: Replaces a range of sibling nodes from the current node to the node specified.
trans-unit.target: Erstatter en rekke likestilte noder fra den gjeldende noden noden som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: The ReplaceRange method replaces a range of sibling nodes from the current node the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on (inclusive) to the node specified by the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> parameter (inclusive).
trans-unit.target: Metoden ReplaceRange erstatter en rekke likestilte noder fra den gjeldende noden den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på (inklusiv) av noden som er angitt av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>parameteren (inklusiv).</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The replacement range is not inserted until the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object is called.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Er ikke satt inn det nye området før den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet kalles.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> </xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.Close%2A>

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> positioned on the last sibling node in the range to replace.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> plasseres på den siste sideordnede-noden i området skal erstatte.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object used to specify the replacement range.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet brukes til å angi det nye området.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> specified is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> specified is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> does not support editing.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> støtter ikke redigering.

trans-unit.source: The last node to replace specified is not a valid sibling node of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Den siste noden erstatte er ikke en gyldig sideordnet node for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Replaces the current node with the content of the string specified.
trans-unit.target: Erstatter den gjeldende noden med innholdet i den angitte strengen.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the new node on completion of the ReplaceSelf method and returns `true`.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på noden for nye på fullføring av metoden ReplaceSelf og returnerer `true`.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is not positioned on the new node after completion of the ReplaceSelf method when the XML input is <xref:System.String.Empty> in which case the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is either positioned on the next sibling node or the parent node if there is no next sibling node to the replaced node and the ReplaceSelf returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er ikke plassert på noden for nye etter fullføring av metoden ReplaceSelf når inndata-XML er <xref:System.String.Empty>da den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>enten plasseres på den neste sideordnede noden eller den overordnede noden hvis det finnes ingen neste sideordnede noden til noden erstattet, og ReplaceSelf returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.String.Empty> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The ReplaceSelf method is valid only when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element, text, processing instruction, or comment node.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden ReplaceSelf er bare gyldig når det <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementet, tekst, behandlingsinstruksjon eller kommentarnode.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - If the XML data string is not well-formed than an exception is thrown and the result of this method is equivalent to calling <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.DeleteSelf%2A> on the current node.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis XML-datastreng ikke er riktig formet enn det et unntak, og resultatet av denne metoden tilsvarer kaller <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.DeleteSelf%2A>på den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.DeleteSelf%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If the XML string contains multiple nodes, all nodes are added and the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the first node in the series of nodes.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis XML-strengen inneholder flere noder, legges til alle noder og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på den første noden i serien med noder.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>krever navneområdet oppløsning, prefikset og navneområdet URI-par må legges til en <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>, og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>metoden må kalles for å angi den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>skal brukes for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: For example, suppose the document contains the following XML nodes.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel: dokumentet inneholder følgende XML-nodene.

trans-unit.source: ``` <bookstore xmlns:bk='urn:samples'> <book bk:ISBN='1-325-0980'> <title>Pride And Prejudice</title> </book> </bookstore> ``` In this case, the following C# code selects the `bk:ISBN` node.
trans-unit.target: ``` <bookstore xmlns:bk='urn:samples'> <book bk:ISBN='1-325-0980'> <title>Pride And Prejudice</title> </book> </bookstore> ```I dette tilfellet følgende C# kode velger den `bk:ISBN` noden.

trans-unit.source: ``` XPathExpression expr = nav.Compile("book/@bk:ISBN"); XmlNamespaceManager mngr = new XmlNamespaceManager(new NameTable()); mngr.AddNamespace("bk","urn:samples"); expr.SetContext(mngr); XPathNodeIterator ni = nav.Select(expr); ``` > [!NOTE] > If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> does not include a prefix, it is assumed that the namespace URI is the empty namespace.
trans-unit.target: ``` XPathExpression expr = nav.Compile("book/@bk:ISBN"); XmlNamespaceManager mngr = new XmlNamespaceManager(new NameTable()); mngr.AddNamespace("bk","urn:samples"); expr.SetContext(mngr); XPathNodeIterator ni = nav.Select(expr); ``` > [!NOTE]> Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>inneholder ikke et prefiks antas det at navneområde-URI er tom navneområdet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: If your XML includes a default namespace, you must still use the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> method and provide an <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> that contains a prefix and namespace URI to handle the default namespace.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-filen inneholder et standard navneområde, må du fortsatt bruke den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>metoden og angi en <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>som inneholder et prefiks og navneområde-URI til å håndtere standard navneområde.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, suppose you have the following XML.
trans-unit.target: Sett for eksempel at du har følgende XML-filen.

trans-unit.source: ``` <bookstore xmlns="http://www.lucernepublishing.com"> <book> <title>Pride And Prejudice</title> </book> </bookstore> ``` In this case, the following C# code selects all book nodes: ``` XmlNamespaceManager nsmgr = new XmlNamespaceManager(nav.NameTable); nsmgr.AddNamespace("ab", "http://www.lucernepublishing.com"); XPathExpression expr; expr = nav.Compile("//ab:book"); expr.SetContext(nsmgr); XPathNodeIterator ni = nav.Select(expr); ``` This method has no effect on the state of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: ``` <bookstore xmlns="http://www.lucernepublishing.com"> <book> <title>Pride And Prejudice</title> </book> </bookstore> ```I dette tilfellet følgende C# kode merker alle book noder: ``` XmlNamespaceManager nsmgr = new XmlNamespaceManager(nav.NameTable); nsmgr.AddNamespace("ab", "http://www.lucernepublishing.com"); XPathExpression expr; expr = nav.Compile("//ab:book"); expr.SetContext(nsmgr); XPathNodeIterator ni = nav.Select(expr); ``` denne metoden har ingen innvirkning på tilstanden for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on an element node with complex content (child elements), calling the SetValue method replaces the child elements with a text node containing the new string value.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er plassert på en elementnode med komplekst innhold (underordnede elementer), kaller SetValue metoden erstatter de underordnede elementene med en text-node som inneholder den nye strengverdien.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: - The SetValue method cannot update the root node or namespace nodes.
trans-unit.target: -Metoden SetValue kan ikke oppdatere rotnode eller navneområdenoder.

trans-unit.source: The new value of the node.
trans-unit.target: Den nye verdien for noden.

trans-unit.source: The value parameter is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Parameteren verdien er <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> is positioned on the root node, a namespace node, or the specified value is invalid.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> er plassert i rotnoden, en navneområdenode eller den angitte verdien er ugyldig.

trans-unit.source: Used by <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"></xref> implementations which provide a "virtualized" XML view over a store, to provide access to underlying objects.
trans-unit.target: Bruk av <xref href="System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator"> </xref> implementeringer som gir en "virtualiserte" XML vise over en butikk, å gi tilgang til underliggende objekter.

trans-unit.source: The UnderlyingObject property can be used by <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> implementations which provide a "virtualized" XML view over a store, to provide access to underlying objects.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen UnderlyingObject kan brukes av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>implementeringer som gir en "virtualiserte" XML vise over en butikk, å gi tilgang til underliggende objekter.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: For example, if an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> object is used to provide a virtual XML view over a Common Language Runtime (CLR) object graph, you may wish to perform XPath queries using the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A> method and then access the CLR objects underlying the selected nodes.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel hvis en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objektet brukes til å angi en virtuell XML-visning over Common Language Runtime (CLR) objektdiagram, kan du vil utføre XPath-spørringer ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A>metoden og tilgang til CLR-objekter underliggende de valgte nodene.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The UnderlyingObject property would expose these underlying objects.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen UnderlyingObject vil utløse disse underliggende objekter.

trans-unit.source: In many cases, this value will be `null`, and the object returned by the UnderlyingObject property will always be implementation specific.
trans-unit.target: Denne verdien blir i mange tilfeller `null`, og objektet som returneres av egenskapen UnderlyingObject vil alltid være implementering.

trans-unit.source: The UnderlyingObject property should preserve object identity and should only be used to return objects that have a one-to-one correspondence to their respective overlaid items.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen UnderlyingObject skal beholde objekt-ID og kan bare brukes til å returnere objekter som har en samsvar for de respektive overlappet elementene.

trans-unit.source: A user should always get the same object on successive visits to the same node using the same <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> object or a cloned one.
trans-unit.target: En bruker må alltid få det samme objektet på etterfølgende besøk på samme node med den samme <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objekt eller en klonede.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The UnderlyingObject property of an <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> object created by an <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> object returns the corresponding <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode>.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > I UnderlyingObject-egenskapen for et <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>objekt som er opprettet av en <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument>tilsvarende <xref:System.Xml.XmlNode>.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNode> -objektet</xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Standard <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueAs%2A> method attempts to convert the value of the current node to the .NET Framework type, specified according to the XPath 2.0 rules for casting the current node's type.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueAs%2A>metoden forsøker å konvertere verdien for den gjeldende noden til .NET Framework-typen, som er angitt i henhold til XPath 2.0-regler for endring av typen for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueAs%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> object is used to resolve namespace prefixes related to type conversions.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>objektet brukes til å løse prefikser for navneområde relatert til datatyper.</xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> has schema or type information (for example, from an <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> object initialized with an XML schema validating <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>), and if the current node is defined as an XML Schema `xs:boolean` type, the ValueAsBoolean property returns the current node's value as an unboxed <xref:System.Boolean> object.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>har skjema-eller typen (for eksempel fra en <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument>objektet initialisert med et XML-skjema validering <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>), og hvis den gjeldende noden er definert som et XML-skjema `xs:boolean` typen egenskapen ValueAsBoolean returnerer verdien for den gjeldende noden som en uinnrammede <xref:System.Boolean>objektet.</xref:System.Boolean> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: However, if the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> does not have any schema or type information, the ValueAsBoolean property attempts to convert the string value of the current node to a <xref:System.Boolean> value, according to the XPath 2.0 casting rules for `xs:boolean`.
trans-unit.target: Men hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>ikke har noen skjemaet eller typen er informasjon ValueAsBoolean egenskapen forsøker å konvertere strengverdien for den gjeldende noden til en <xref:System.Boolean>verdi, i henhold til XPath 2.0 endring regler for `xs:boolean`.</xref:System.Boolean> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Gets the current node's value as a <xref:System.Double>.
trans-unit.target: Henter den gjeldende noden verdien som en <xref:System.Double>.</xref:System.Double>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> has schema or type information (for example, from an <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> object initialized with an XML schema validating <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>), and if the current node is defined as an XML Schema `xs:double` type, the ValueAsDouble property returns the current node's value as an unboxed <xref:System.Double> object.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>har skjema-eller typen (for eksempel fra en <xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument>objektet initialisert med et XML-skjema validering <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>), og hvis den gjeldende noden er definert som et XML-skjema `xs:double` typen egenskapen ValueAsDouble returnerer verdien for den gjeldende noden som en uinnrammede <xref:System.Double>objektet.</xref:System.Double> </xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xml.XmlDocument> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: However, if the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> does not have any schema or type information, the ValueAsDouble property attempts to convert the string value of the current node to a <xref:System.Double> value, according to the XPath 2.0 casting rules for `xsd:double`.
trans-unit.target: Men hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>ikke har noen skjemaet eller typen er informasjon ValueAsDouble egenskapen forsøker å konvertere strengverdien for den gjeldende noden til en <xref:System.Double>verdi, i henhold til XPath 2.0 endring regler for `xsd:double`.</xref:System.Double> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: Gets the .NET Framework <xref:System.Type> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Henter .NET Framework <xref:System.Type>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Type>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A> property gets the .NET Framework <xref:System.Type> of the typed value of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>egenskapen henter .NET Framework <xref:System.Type>typeangitt-verdien for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Type> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, an element of type `xs:int` would have a <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A> of <xref:System.Int32> by default.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel et element av typen `xs:int` må en <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>av <xref:System.Int32>som standard.</xref:System.Int32> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>

trans-unit.source: However, the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A> could be any one of the valid types that can be mapped to `xs:int` such as <xref:System.Int16> or <xref:System.Double>.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>kan være en av de gyldige typene som kan tilordnes til `xs:int` for eksempel <xref:System.Int16>eller <xref:System.Double>.</xref:System.Double> </xref:System.Int16> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathItem.ValueType%2A>

trans-unit.source: If a node has no type, this is equivalent to the type annotation on the node being `xdt:untypedAtomic`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis en node har ingen type, tilsvarer typen merknaden på noden som `xdt:untypedAtomic`.

trans-unit.source: In this case, the ValueType property returns a string for the node.
trans-unit.target: I dette tilfellet returnerer egenskapen verditype en streng for noden.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Type Support in the System.Xml Classes](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil ha mer informasjon, se [typen støtte i System.Xml klassene](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework <xref:System.Type> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: .NET Framework <xref:System.Type>for den gjeldende noden.</xref:System.Type>

trans-unit.source: The default value is <xref:System.String>.
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er <xref:System.String>.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Streams the current node and its child nodes to the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object specified.
trans-unit.target: Strømmer den gjeldende noden og de underordnede nodene til det <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet som er angitt.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Namespace declarations for the in-scope namespaces of the current node are inserted into the XML streamed to the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object specified.
trans-unit.target: Namespace deklareringer for navneområdene i omfanget for den gjeldende noden er satt inn i XML direkteavspilte til det <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet som er angitt.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: For example, if the WriteSubtree method is called on the first `book` element of the `books.xml` file, the `http://www.contoso.com/books` namespace declaration made at the top of the XML document will appear in the XML streamed to the <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object specified as shown in the following example.
trans-unit.target: Hvis metoden WriteSubtree kalles for eksempel på først `book` element av den `books.xml` filen i `http://www.contoso.com/books` navneområdedeklarasjon gjort øverst i XML-dokumentet vises i XML-direkteavspilte til det <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objektet som er angitt som vises i følgende eksempel.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: ``` <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <book genre="autobiography" publicationdate="1981" ISBN="1-861003-11-0" xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"> <title>The Autobiography of Benjamin Franklin</title> <author> <first-name>Benjamin</first-name> <last-name>Franklin</last-name> </author> <price>8.99</price> </book> ``` > [!NOTE] > The WriteSubtree method does not affect the position of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: ``` <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <book genre="autobiography" publicationdate="1981" ISBN="1-861003-11-0" xmlns="http://www.contoso.com/books"> <title>The Autobiography of Benjamin Franklin</title> <author> <first-name>Benjamin</first-name> <last-name>Franklin</last-name> </author> <price>8.99</price> </book> ``` > [!NOTE]> Metoden WriteSubtree påvirker plasseringen av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter> object to stream to.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>objekt stream til.</xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>

trans-unit.source: Gets the `xml:lang` scope for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Henter den `xml:lang` omfanget for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: In the example XML below, when the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is positioned on the `name` element, the XmlLang property returns a scope of `en-us` indicating that the node is in the scope of a `xml:lang="en-us"` attribute.
trans-unit.target: I eksemplet XML nedenfor, når den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>plasseres på den `name` elementet egenskapen XmlLang returnerer en konsekvensene av `en-us` som angir at noden er i området for en `xml:lang="en-us"` attributtet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> that contains the value of the `xml:lang` scope, or <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> if the current node has no `xml:lang` scope value to return.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.String>som inneholder verdien for den `xml:lang` omfang, eller <xref:System.String?displayProperty=fullName> hvis den gjeldende noden ingen har `xml:lang` område verdien som skal returneres.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Gets the <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaType"></xref> information for the current node.
trans-unit.target: Henter den <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaType"> </xref> informasjon for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the XmlType property.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta ved XmlType-egenskapen.

trans-unit.source: - The XmlType property is `null`, unless the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.Validity%2A> property of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> is set to <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaValidity?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: -Egenskapen XmlType `null`, med mindre <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.Validity%2A>egenskapen for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>egenskapen for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>er satt til <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaValidity?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaValidity?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.Validity%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If this node is valid, the XmlType property is the same as the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A> property of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>, unless this node is a member of a union.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis denne noden er gyldig, egenskapen XmlType er lik den <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A>for den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>for den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>, med mindre denne noden er medlem av en sammenslåing.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.SchemaType%2A>

trans-unit.source: - If this node is a member of a union, the XmlType property is the same as the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.MemberType%2A> property of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> property of this <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis denne noden er medlem av en union, tilsvarer egenskapen XmlType <xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.MemberType%2A>egenskapen for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A>egenskapen for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SchemaInfo%2A> </xref:System.Xml.Schema.IXmlSchemaInfo.MemberType%2A>
